defaultCarbon Capture and Storage 
default(CCS) is a critical 
defaulttechnology with potential to make a significant impact in reducing CO2 emissions from the power and industrial sectors in the UK and worldwide. CCS offers the 
defaultopportunity
default to continue to utilise fossil fuels, and enjoy the energy security benefits this brin
defaultgs, but with vastly reduced emissions. CCS is also a critical part of meeting emissions reduction targets in a cost effective way. 
defaultWhilst CCS is not currently competitive with other low carbon forms of generation
default 
defaultthere is the potential for costs to fall si
defaultgnificantly as deployment increases. 
defaultModelling in both the UK and internationally indicates it will be significantly cheaper to meet emissions reduction targets with CCS in the energy mix, rather than without. 
default2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, there are currently
default a range of
default techn
defaultical and economic barriers to deployment
default which impede projects coming forward independently in the UK
default and elsewhere
default. In recognition of the 
defaultpotential of CCS
default, the Government has introduced a comprehensive package of financial and regulatory support designed 
defaultto 
defaulthelp 
defaultovercome these barriers.
default The Commercialisation Programme will demonstrate the full integrated CCS chain at commercial scale, proving the technology and significantly reducing the 
defaultcommercial and financial 
defaultrisks currently associated with it. The Gove
defaultrnment’s wider policies, as set out in the CCS Roadmap, look beyond the first projects and are designed to build a strong and successful CCS industry. 
default3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 
defaultmeasures introduced by
default Government 
defaultare amongst the most 
defaultcomprehensive
default anywhere in the world. 
defaultThe Gove
defaultrnment is also
default continually 
defaultengaging with other countries worldwide
default to promote CCS and learn from their experience. We are also in close dialogue 
defaultwith the industry in the UK to drive forward development and deployment of this technology.  The Government wel
defaultcomes the Committee’s investigation into Carbon Capture and Storage and 
defaultthe contribution it can make to the Government’s programmes in this area
default. 
