defaultCarbon Capture and Storage (CCS) is a chain of technologies designed to remove the greenhouse gas carbon dioxide (CO2) from power and industrial sources and transport it for safe permanent storage in saline aquifers or depleted oil and gas fields. 
defaultI
defaultt is
default th
defaulte only technology that 
defaulthas the potential to
default 
defaultturn high carbon fuels into genuinely low carbon electricity
default and to decarbonise
default many
default industrial activities. 
