defaultHSE believes that existing legislation will allow for effective inspection and enforcement of health and safety standards associated with CCS projects. The Pipelines Safety Regulations 1996 also imposes general duties on all pipeline operators, including a
defaultppropriate design, safety systems, maintenance, suitability to convey fluids, construction and installation, and prevention of accidental damage. 
default54.
