defaultl be required to produce a safety case under the permissioning regime set out in the Control of Major Accident Hazards Regulations 1999 (COMAH). The COMAH Regulations are enforced by a body called the COMAH Competent
default Authority, which
default brings together 
defaultthe re
defaultlevant
default government bodies of Health and Safety Executive (HSE) and Environment Agency (EA) in England and Wales, and the HSE and Scottish Environment Protection Agency (SEPA) in Scotland.
